47
00:03:06,945 --> 00:03:09,586
which was when we brought Kara Ellison on, a very talented writer,

48
00:03:09,966 --> 00:03:13,468
and we all committed to the idea of trying to make it into a black comedy

49
00:03:13,928 --> 00:03:16,849
as opposed to what was done in these pages, which is

50
00:03:17,569 --> 00:03:21,671
just a really, really desperate sad tale of someone who was alone in space.

51
00:03:32,615 --> 00:03:38,861
Okay, what we've got here is a very early mock-up of how we might try and do a cutscene

52
00:03:39,682 --> 00:03:43,726
in a comic book form, and this is the one that would sort of set up and open the game

53
00:03:44,286 --> 00:03:46,368
that Kara and I worked on together.

54
00:03:47,129 --> 00:03:53,635
We did decide at the end that it was far too long, and consequently, we re-approached how

55
00:03:53,655 --> 00:03:58,039
we did these, and we made them much more brief, and sort of much more to the point.

56
00:03:58,657 --> 00:04:02,921
but I think this is a fascinating thing to look at, especially if you're a fan.

57
00:04:02,961 --> 00:04:05,864
Like, I've actually really enjoyed looking at all this stuff myself this week.

58
00:04:06,424 --> 00:04:09,648
And you can see just how different even the tone was.

59
00:04:09,828 --> 00:04:15,734
It's got elements of Kara's jokes and the Douglas Adams influence and everything else,

60
00:04:16,534 --> 00:04:18,316
but it isn't quite the same as what we wound up with.

61
00:04:25,087 --> 00:04:26,907
I love you all.

62
00:05:15,423 --> 00:05:19,544
So, to just finish off the topic of the comic book look I was talking about, how everything

63
00:05:19,584 --> 00:05:20,365
needed to be a comic.

64
00:05:21,057 --> 00:05:26,781
These are early concepts of how the campaign map, the loadout screen, and the machine map might look.

65
00:05:26,981 --> 00:05:30,844
We didn't know at this point. This was all just done in Photoshop. We didn't have anything really

